      "side": 1,
      "message": "Clearly this class has been almost entirely modified, although the actual logic that draws the existing joins is more or less unchanged.\n\nThe JoinProc pattern was good for generality but only if all joins need more or less the same parameters. Building the parameters into an object allows more flexibility -- the new code only calculates curvatures when they\u0027re needed -- and making the setters inline will (should?) minimize the overhead. JoinProc also had the disadvantage of repeating the \"inner\" join logic (\"which is inner and outer, is an inner join needed?\") in each of the join styles.",
      "revId": "e3a38dc6a68d4e17dd926360802e00bfb8278d01",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
