      "writtenOn": "2020-07-16T23:38:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "NVPR supports a version of truncated miters that I\u0027ve added above. The documentation (https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL/extensions/NV/NV_path_rendering.txt#:~:text\u003dThe%20MITER_TRUNCATE_NV%20join,the%20miter%20limit. ) suggests that the implementation should match the miter-clip spec but it doesn\u0027t quite. One problem is that the miterlimit is interpreted differently for TRUNCATE and REVERT, as I\u0027ve noted. The other is that the clip line doesn\u0027t seem to be calculated correctly.\n\nMy email on this subject to nvpr-support@nvidia.com seems to have gone into /dev/null. It would probably be best to add kMiterClip_join to the reject list here before merging this work. I didn\u0027t do so so that reviewers could verify the problem for themselves by running \n\nviewer --slide StrokeJoins --pr nvpr --msaa 4\n\nand flipping between raster and nvpr with \"d\".",
      "revId": "e3a38dc6a68d4e17dd926360802e00bfb8278d01",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
