      "writtenOn": "2020-07-16T23:38:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Adding miter-clip to this renderer and its current triangle-fan join model would be fairly straightforward. There are two approaches to parameterizing the clip line; I\u0027m not sure which is best. If we get that far I can chat with Chris Dalton about it.\n\nDoing an arcs join in CCPR would have been tricky. It may be easier in this context because it looks easier to add \"custom\" code. The current round join is a triangle fan. If each arc is parameterized as center/radius and start/end point one could build a triangle strip by (speaking informally) breaking both arcs into the same number of vertices (as with a fan) but alternating between them. There are some special cases (sometimes one side is a line, sometimes a point).",
